PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- Nine people -- including a British UNMIK policeman, a Dutch woman and two Serbs -- were injured when a hand grenade exploded in a cafÃ© in the Serb quarter of Kosovska Mitrovica on Saturday (26 August). 
